# Application layer rules

Full handler templates live in `src/LoreWeave.Application/CLAUDE.md`. This
rule is the short reminder of the cross-cutting Application-layer conventions.

- Every operation is a `record Command` or `record Query` plus an
  `IAsyncRequestHandler<TRequest, Result<...>>`.
- `LogFilter<TRequest, TResponse>` wraps all handlers automatically — no
  per-handler logging setup.
- Handlers return one of:
  - `Result<TValue, Exception>` — success carries a value.
  - `Result<Exception>` — void-like success.
- Commands: always `await using var transaction = await _transactionFactory.CreateAsync();`
  Commit on success, rollback in `catch`.
- Queries are read-only — no commit/rollback.
- Domain entities never leak from queries — always map to a payload first.
- Register every handler in `IoC/HandlerConfiguration.cs` with
  `.AddAsyncRequestHandler<TYourHandler>()`.